- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a high-performance metaheuristic for solving the problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses approximating matrices by rank-one binary matrices. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses evolutionary algorithms to solve the problem. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper discusses applications of the problem in computing the cut-norm of a matrix and solving optimization problems.
